./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1914:CHANGELOG.md:796:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
