./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1924:CHANGELOG.md:870:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1929:CHANGELOG.md:890:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1930:CHANGELOG.md:892:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1931:CHANGELOG.md:893:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1934:CHANGELOG.md:910:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1936:CHANGELOG.md:912:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1939:CHANGELOG.md:917:- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1940:CHANGELOG.md:919:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1943:CHANGELOG.md:943:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1945:CHANGELOG.md:946:- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1947:CHANGELOG.md:955:- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1948:CHANGELOG.md:956:- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1950:CHANGELOG.md:962:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1951:CHANGELOG.md:963:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1952:CHANGELOG.md:965:- Gave the named house patches real musical identities instead of just voice pools: `score_from_mood()` is now patch-aware, so melody contour, bass/comping pattern, progression bank, dynamics, and register spread all change with the active house patch.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1960:CHANGELOG.md:1002:- Added a queue-backed Telegram `/monitor` built-in so live queue progress and active task status come from the authority DB instead of stale routed status text.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1961:CHANGELOG.md:1003:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:1962:CHANGELOG.md:1007:- Added the missing `OPT-005` half-hour Telegram heartbeat in the live daemon scheduler, including uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, pet XP summary, and Observatory logging.
