./sdp/logs/Lead_T-048a_1779560748.log:12411:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:5:CypherClaw already composes legible music: score trees, section functions, production profiles, genre strategies, SenseWeave mappings. But the path from composed score to synthesized audio still renders too rigidly. Phrases don't breathe. Repeated motifs don't vary. Silence is a byproduct of scheduling rather than an intentional voice. Sensors occasionally read like one-to-one controllers rather than shaping aggregate intent. The result is the "almost-human" failure mode: structurally competent, expressively flat.
