\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T19:11:00.623899+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 3104.134, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-021@20260416T054258Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-021@20260416T054258Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:03:07.350538+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 477.768, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-018@20260416T054258Za completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-018@20260416T054258Za\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:13:00.719558+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 4ff5be6..16ccb8c 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,288 +1,163 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**SHA-256:** `2ed4ef622028ccd47ff58a0ebf97bf53ad6c16901cc35550eaa31b8bdd359ca9`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Captured:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472655+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**SHA-256:** `65bcff28a80825e9c3dd33ed94a39f17a86a9e5d3d4c81aa9c271db4fb9b06ba`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Captured:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.336565+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ## Overview\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-CypherClaw now has a working score-tree and tracker-based songwriting spine,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-but the musical education layer still needs to be encoded as software behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-This PRD translates the CypherClaw Music Production Course into implementation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-work: theory, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, mixing, mastering, critical listening,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-SenseWeave interpretation, Theramini ensemble behavior, genre literacy, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-30-minute dramatic-arc production practice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The goal is not to store a static course document. The goal is to make the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-course operational. CypherClaw should consult these ideas while composing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-persist the resulting production choices in score trees and tracker metadata,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verify them with tests/audio proxies, and use them during live playback.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The production course is organized around the 30-minute dramatic arc:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Divination:** sparse listening, environmental responsiveness, wide space\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Emergence:** motifs and pulse forming, modal identity, opening filters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Conversation:** dialogue, counterpoint, call-and-response, development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Convergence:** density, climax, harmonic/rhythmic/timbral saturation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Crystallization:** resolution, reduction, memory, reverb tail, archive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Every requirement below should make that arc more musically literate and more\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verifiable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Depends on:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/sdp/prd-songwriter-emsd-completion.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-emsd-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  master bus, sample, self-listener, repertoire, and Theramini modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Key files and modules:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/form_grammar.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/reharmonizer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/hook_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker_runtime.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/arrangement_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/mix_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/ear_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sound_palette_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/dsp_scene_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/theramini_duet.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/repertoire_memory.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- new production-course support modules under `my-claw/tools/senseweave/`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Current State Analysis\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Implemented Foundation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Score trees already represent commission, brief, form, motifs, sections,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  harmonic plan, arrangement plan, narrative map, and metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The composer can compile approved score trees into tracker scenes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The runtime can schedule tracker rows, apply some row automation, and publish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  current state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Harmony, hooks, arrangement, mix, sound palette, sample, DSP, ear, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  repertoire helpers exist as first-pass modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- EMSD curriculum scaffolds exist and can be used as reference/curriculum\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  targets.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Remaining Production Gaps\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Pitch, scale, chord, voicing, and functional-harmony knowledge is scattered\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and not consistently encoded in one verified musical vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Rhythm currently uses duration cells, but not enough meter, swing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  polyrhythm, phrase breath, metric modulation, or groove intent.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Counterpoint and motivic development exist only in partial metadata; they\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  need rules that can shape independent lanes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Synthesis, production, and mix choices are not yet explicitly selected from\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  the course concepts per arc phase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Critical listening metrics exist as first-pass proxies but do not yet feed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  production choices strongly enough.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- SenseWeave mappings need musical interpretation rules for room, membrane,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Genre literacy is not yet a strategy library that can influence form,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  rhythm, harmony, sound design, and arrangement.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The 30-minute production score needs to become a runtime phase profile,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  not only prose.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Encode the course as a runtime production knowledge base with typed,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  testable concepts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make pitch, harmony, rhythm, counterpoint, synthesis, mix, and production\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  decisions visible in score-tree and tracker metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Improve long-form musical variety without losing live safety.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Give each 30-minute arc phase a coherent production profile.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make SenseWeave and Theramini inputs musically interpretable through course\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  concepts instead of arbitrary parameter mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Add automated verification that catches unmusical regressions such as flat\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  loops, single-note drones, harsh registers, muddy mixes, missing transitions,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and phase-inappropriate density.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Non-Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not replace the existing score-tree/tracker runtime.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require external music APIs or copyrighted training material.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require real SuperCollider rendering for every unit test. Deterministic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  metadata tests and synthetic audio proxies are acceptable where live rendering\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  is impractical.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not make every piece complex. Divination and Crystallization may be sparse\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  by design, and micro pieces remain valid when complete.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not hardcode one style as CypherClaw's identity. Genre literacy should be\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  a strategy vocabulary, not an imitation machine.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Product Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-|---|---|---|---|---|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-001 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | MUST | T1 | - course concepts are represented as typed data or markdown references with stable IDs<br/>- arc-phase profiles exist for Divination, Emergence, Conversation, Convergence, and Crystallization<br/>- tests verify all required chapters/phase profiles are present and loadable |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-003 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | MUST | T1 | - triads, seventh chords, extended chords, altered dominants, suspended/add chords, drop voicings, close/open voicings, and rootless/guide-tone voicings are supported<br/>- voicing engine respects register limits and configured spacing<br/>- tests verify chord pitch classes, unique voicings, range safety, and smooth voice-leading choices |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-004 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | MUST | T1 | - harmonic planner can label tonic, subdominant, dominant, secondary dominant, modal-interchange, tritone-sub, chromatic-mediant, pedal, planing, and modulation functions<br/>- score trees expose harmonic function and transition intent per section<br/>- tests verify cadence resolution, pivot/common-tone modulation continuity, and phase-appropriate tension levels |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-005 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | MUST | T1 | - rhythm engine supports 4/4, 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8, free/rubato, swing, shuffle, dotted cells, push/pull, polyrhythm, polymeter, and metric modulation<br/>- tracker metadata carries meter, subdivision, swing ratio, groove timing, and phrase breath without breaking deterministic row scheduling<br/>- tests verify IOI ratios, swing offsets, polyrhythm cycle length, and phase-specific meter policies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-006 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | MUST | T1 | - arrangement/compiler can choose contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, and completion relationships between lanes<br/>- dissonance and resolution rules are available as metadata checks<br/>- tests verify independent lane contours, staggered climaxes, and no accidental lane crowding |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-007 | Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. | SHOULD | T2 | - composer can request pitch-class sets, spectral partial-derived harmony, just-intonation ratios, and 24-TET/ratio pitch events when phase/style permits<br/>- SenseWeave spectral analysis can seed harmonic material<br/>- tests verify generated material remains bounded and tagged as post-tonal/spectral/microtonal |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-008 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | MUST | T1 | - registry covers subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT processing with safe parameter ranges and arc-phase affinities<br/>- score tree or tracker scenes can request synthesis architecture by production role<br/>- tests verify each architecture has role tags, macro controls, safe ranges, and fallbacks |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-009 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | MUST | T1 | - mix engine assigns sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, and air lanes to roles<br/>- production metadata includes HPF/LPF/EQ intent for bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, and Theramini lanes<br/>- tests verify role frequency lanes avoid primary masking and preserve bass center policy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-010 | Add dynamics, compression, sidechain, and deference policy. | MUST | T1 | - production profile maps arc phase to dynamic range, compression intensity, transient policy, and sidechain/deference rules<br/>- Theramini and environmental transients can request generated-material ducking or silence<br/>- tests verify dynamic targets, sidechain metadata, and no over-compression in Divination/Crystallization |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-011 | Add spatial, reverb, and delay production profiles. | MUST | T1 | - phase profiles define stereo width, near/far depth, reverb size/decay/damping, delay style, and transition-space behavior<br/>- tracker scenes expose spatial intent and reverb/delay sends<br/>- tests verify wide sparse openings, clearer Conversation space, focused Convergence, and long Crystallization tails |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-012 | Complete mastering and loudness policy for installation playback. | MUST | T1 | - master policy targets installation-safe LUFS/peak ranges, limiter ceiling, broad EQ intent, and phase-specific dynamic contrast<br/>- automated proxies catch clipping, silence, harshness, and low-end runaway<br/>- tests verify master profiles and synthetic render/loudness proxies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-014 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-016 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | MUST | T1 | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-017 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | MUST | T1 | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify the five-phase contour and phase-specific production metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-018 | Add phase-transition comp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      paramsSerializer: [Function: paramsSerializer],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      validateStatus: [Function: validateStatus],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      errorRedactor: [Function: defaultErrorRedactor]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    data: '[{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 429,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"No capacity avai