ps.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  the implemented code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRun before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll must pass.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260416T054258Z_1776373994.log:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T21:17:07.044Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"grep_search\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"grep_