CHANGELOG.md:777:- Added depth-2 pareidolia-characters end-to-end test coverage (frac-0100): `tests/test_pareidolia_characters.py` now includes `PareidoliaCharactersEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/pareidolia.py` PARE-003 surface through one multi-group scene composition flow: `select_palette(hour=10, mood="happy")` resolves to `PALETTES["day_happy"]`, the `CHARACTER_REGISTRY` maps one primary name and one `the …` alias per organism group (sensors → `draw_membrane`, voices → `draw_poet`, outputs → `draw_speaker`, bridges → `draw_weaver`) and each direct draw call produces a non-empty RGBA canvas, `render_panel` dispatches a four-character `PanelSpec` mixing primary names and `the …` aliases with a rock element and dialogue overlay, `render_scene` dispatches the same four primary names plus an `unknown_entity` that falls back to `draw_character` under a `WeatherEffects(cloud_count=2, show_sun=True, star_count=4)` overlay, and a combined diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_pareidolia_characters_depth.py` pins the pareidolia-characters test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4594 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:961:- Added depth-2 collaborative canvas helpers (frac-0007): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/collaborative_canvas.py` now exposes `canvas_layer_manifest`, `canvas_summary`, and `render_text_canvas` so the shared installation canvas can produce stable operator-readable layer metadata, meaningful layer/count/bounds summaries, and a deterministic fixed-size text rendering from persisted canvas state. Existing layer mutation and JSON state round-trip behavior is preserved; `tests/test_collaborative_canvas_depth.py` pins manifest ordering, summary counts and bounds, priority-based text composition, JSON round-trip rendering, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:1069:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
