# holdenu-api — Cloudflare Worker

Backs holdenu.com with the release flow, public catalog data, audio
streaming, and (Phase 3) Stripe commerce.

## First-time setup

```bash
cd worker
npm install
npx wrangler login

# Create resources (one-time)
npx wrangler d1 create holdenu                # → paste database_id into wrangler.toml
npx wrangler r2 bucket create holdenu-media

# Edit wrangler.toml: replace REPLACE_WITH_* placeholders

# Migrate D1 (local first)
npm run db:migrate:local
npm run db:migrate:remote

# Set secrets (production)
npx wrangler secret put ADMIN_TOKEN
npx wrangler secret put STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
npx wrangler secret put STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
npx wrangler secret put RESEND_API_KEY
```

For local development create `worker/.dev.vars`:

```
ADMIN_TOKEN=dev-token-change-me
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
```

## Run

```bash
npm run dev          # serves at http://localhost:8787
```

The workspace (catalog-explorer) reads `HOLDENU_API_BASE` from
`data/local.js` (gitignored) and falls back to localhost:8787 in dev.

## Routes

| Method | Path                          | Auth   | Purpose                          |
|--------|-------------------------------|--------|----------------------------------|
| GET    | /api/releases                 | public | Visible releases + tracks        |
| GET    | /api/public-annotations       | public | Sanitized annotations            |
| GET    | /api/stream/:trackId          | public | Byte-range audio proxy from R2   |
| GET    | /download/:token              | public | Paid download (token from order) |
| POST   | /api/cypherclaw/segment      | admin  | Store live CypherClaw segment in R2 |
| GET    | /api/cypherclaw/live-midi    | public | WebSocket to the live CypherClaw MIDI room |
| POST   | /api/checkout                 | public | Create Stripe Checkout Session   |
| POST   | /api/webhook/stripe           | sig    | Stripe webhook (sig-verified)    |
| POST   | /api/release                  | admin  | Create/update release event      |
| POST   | /api/upload-url               | admin  | Sign R2 upload URL               |
| POST   | /api/sync                     | admin  | Mirror workspace annotations     |

Admin endpoints expect `Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>`.

