CHANGELOG.md:885:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:887:- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe → summarize → render → main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:889:- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:891:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw memory journal helpers (frac-0051): `promptclaw/memory.py` now exposes a frozen `MemoryEntry` dataclass plus typed helpers `format_run_block`, `parse_memory_log`, and `summarize_memory_log`, and `MemoryStore` gains `entries`, `latest_entry`, and `summary` read-side methods so callers and operator diagnostics can render a single run's memory block, parse the project memory file back into structured entries (run id, title, status, lead, verifier, final phase, body), and emit a JSON-safe aggregate (entry count, latest run id, sorted status counts, sorted lead-agent counts excluding the `n/a` placeholder). `MemoryStore.append_run_summary` now delegates block rendering to `format_run_block` so the on-disk markdown shape stays byte-identical for orchestrator clarification-pause and final-summary writes. `tests/test_promptclaw_memory_depth.py` pins canonical block layout, `n/a` agent fallbacks, append/parse round-trip, empty-input handling, JSON-safe summary aggregation, `n/a` lead exclusion, store read helpers (including missing-file path), and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` remains the regression anchor for end-to-end run behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:893:- Added depth-2 image API schema summaries (frac-0050): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py` now exposes `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES`, `ACTIVE_JOB_STATUSES`, frozen `JobLifecycleSummary` and `InternalSpecProfile` dataclasses, and typed helpers `is_terminal_status`, `build_job_lifecycle_summary`, `summarize_status_response`, `build_internal_spec_profile`, and `summarize_internal_spec`. The helpers give operator logs and dashboards JSON-safe lifecycle/spec metadata including terminal-state classification, output counts, error flags, image dimensions, pixel count, megapixels, prompt previews, style presence, model overrides, and content-piece IDs without changing any Pydantic request/response fields or runtime behavior. `tests/test_image_api_schemas_depth.py` pins the new helper surface and fractal depth >= 2; existing parser, worker, app, jobs DB, S3 uploader, startup identity, and narrative ASGI startup anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:895:- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
